== English ==
=== Adjective ===
'''coloured'''
# Having a particular [[:w:colour|colour]] or kind of colour
#* The room was '''coloured''' red, with a dark-'''coloured''' rug.
# Having prominent colours; [[colourful]]
#* The singer wore a '''coloured''' shirt.
# Influenced pervasively but subtly
#* My opinions are '''coloured''' by my upbringing.
# (''older usage, potentially offensive'') Skin colour being other than the white, Anglo-Saxon race, particularly as an African American, or black person.
#* Being of an older generation, they considered themselves "'''coloured''' ladies"''
# (''potentially offensive'') In the context of [[apartheid]], neither "black" nor "white"

